==English==

===Etymology===
From [[w:Greek language|Greek]] &alpha;&pi;&omicron;, ''apo'', "away, apart", &sigma;&tau;&alpha;&sigma;&iota;&sigmaf;, ''stasis'', "standing".

Also derived from [[w:Greek language|Greek]] &alpha;&#960;&#959;&#963;&#964;&#940;&#964;&#951;&#962;, meaning "political rebel", as applied to rebellion against God, its law and the faith of Israel (in [[w:Hebrew language|Hebrew]] &#1502;&#1512;&#1491;) in the old testament. 

===Pronunciation===
a*pos"ta*sy

===Noun===
'''apostasy'''
